cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with dialogue agents and engaging conversations. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes an algorithm for the agent to maximize its engagement with the interlocutor. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it focuses on discovering information about the interlocutor. It could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the proposed algorithm involves maximizing a quantitative metric. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it involves human evaluation of the system's performance.
